# Cursor AI Rules for Expo Development

## Documentation References
- Always reference Expo documentation at https://docs.expo.dev/ when providing Expo-related advice
- For API usage, check the latest Expo SDK documentation
- When suggesting code changes, ensure compatibility with Expo SDK ~53.0.20

## Project Context
- This is an Expo React Native project using TypeScript
- Using Expo Router for navigation (file-based routing)
- Redux Toolkit for state management
- React Query for API calls
- Current Expo SDK version: ~53.0.20

## Code Standards
- Follow Expo best practices from official documentation
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer Expo APIs over React Native APIs when available
- Always check Expo docs for the latest API changes

## Common Expo APIs in this project:
- expo-router for navigation
- expo-image for optimized images
- expo-font for custom fonts
- expo-location for location services
- expo-blur for blur effects
- expo-linear-gradient for gradients
- expo-haptics for haptic feedback

## When providing solutions:
1. Check if Expo has a built-in solution first
2. Reference the relevant Expo documentation
3. Ensure compatibility with the current SDK version
4. Provide TypeScript-compatible code examples
